lyrics:
[verse]
In a small town where the birds would sing
I met a girl who made my heart take wing
Her name was Lena, like a summer breeze
With eyes that sparkled and a heart at ease

[chorus]
Oh, Lena, you're the sun in my sky
With each passing day, I can't help but sigh
Your laughter brings me joy, your touch is pure bliss
Lena, my love, you're the one I will miss
